Nowadays , the use of the sociall media platforms is a commonplace in our lives .
In an increasingly globalised world , such platforms even enhance and compliccates the link between indivduals in the world .
Thanks to them , people can get to know one another online , without having to travel to meet up for business purposes for companies or personal reasons .
However , it is also bring some social changes whereby such virtual worlds are overtaking the real-life world , resulting in some negative impacts in individuaul 's daily lives and therefore becoming a large problem in society as a whole .
As people spend more and more time on such social media sites , the importance of the face-to-face human contacts has decresed .
As people feel more confident online where they do not have to face in real-life on the spot , they feel more comfortable and thus prefer communicating online .
This results in a lack of interpersonal skills in the individual , especially the young students as they always have option to turn back to the real-life and go online .
This becomes a huge problem when they have no choice but have to face things in real life .
As they are used to have an online avatar , they may lose their self-identity in real life and may not realise to interact in real-life .
